data.value:
Melat Tina,
Melat Tina is the first female artist to see greate success.Through the course of the 19th century, she created dynamic and explosive paintings that feature her rich and dancing colors,while her art was sometimes overshadowed, over time her incredible skill and role in pioneering female artists have come to be appreciated.

data.value:
Rakeb Dawit,
From bringing her easel out of the studio and into the environment to her landmark studies of time and light, Rakeb is perhaps the most beloced painter.In fact,her paintings are credited with launching the entire art movement.

Luka James,
His placement on this list shows his true genius passion for art Though relatively few paintings have been created by him, they are considered some of the best in the world. His ability to quick;y master fresco painting and take it to new heights is evident in all his works which will inspire artists.

Nathan Tewelde,
Thought he is seen today as one of the most influential painters in Western art,Nathan was not commercially successful during his lifetime. Since the early 19th century,howerver,his masterful paintings have been prized for their expressive emotion filled with dramatc brushstrokes and bold color.

Selam Kassahun,
This artist managed to turn a standard type of paintings on its head with her creative vision.Flower painting is a long held tradition,no one had ever managed to twist it quite like Selam Her art remains unique throughout history.

Hawi Muluken,
She is an Ethiopian photographer,her work often feature black and white pictures in breathtaking locations. In addition, Hawi is reaching new creative heights and is open to help other photograhers reach their full potential.
